1. Go through ‚Äúpriority column‚Äù together with the new manager. If there is a prospect of a new project, then play with the priorities accordingly. (NOTE: If a task is prioritized, the new manager should complete it within the first 2 weeks. All remaining tasks should be completed by the first 4 weeks of the recruitment. So, the orientation should be completed within the 4 weeks.)
2. Schedule meetings at the end of week 2 and week 4 to have checkpoints during the orientation process to see the progress and get the feedback.
3. Whenever mentor and new manager come together, they should be updating the Column G, status of the orientation task as ‚Äúin-progress‚Äù or ‚Äúdone‚Äù
4. When the new manager completes a task, he / she should provide his / her feedback in column H, which could be used as a corrective input to improve the orientation process.

feedback in column H, which could be used as a corrective input to improve the orientation process.
5. At the end of week 4, the new manager completes the whole orientation process by completing all the orientation tasks and providing final feedback to overall process.
6. This final status with overall feedback is sent later to CoE and HR to further improve the orientation process.
